00:58:01.040 --> 00:58:04.730
So what we're charged with
doing is looking at how news

00:58:04.730 --> 00:58:06.460
and public affairs
came into being

00:58:06.460 --> 00:58:08.190
and how it evolved
in public media.

00:58:08.190 --> 00:58:09.820
Jim, I'm going to
start with you,

00:58:09.820 --> 00:58:12.100
you were there almost
at the beginning.

00:58:12.100 --> 00:58:15.470
When you came to Washington
it was all about Watergate.

00:58:15.470 --> 00:58:18.270
We saw that clip, what happened?

00:58:18.270 --> 00:58:19.570
&gt;&gt; Jim Lehrer: Well
the Watergate -

00:58:19.570 --> 00:58:22.770
the Watergate hearings
really did -

00:58:22.770 --> 00:58:25.420
that was the water
shed event for news

00:58:25.420 --> 00:58:27.880
and public affairs
on public television.

00:58:27.880 --> 00:58:30.990
Up to that point the stations

00:58:30.990 --> 00:58:32.680
and the public was
generally divided

00:58:32.680 --> 00:58:37.220
over whether they even needed
any more news and public affairs

00:58:37.220 --> 00:58:39.770
on television beyond
what was already there

00:58:39.770 --> 00:58:41.370
on commercial television.

00:58:41.370 --> 00:58:44.070
The Nixon Administration
particularly didn't think there

00:58:44.070 --> 00:58:46.910
was a need for any more
news and public affairs

00:58:46.910 --> 00:58:48.470
on public broadcasting.

00:58:48.470 --> 00:58:49.770
But the Watergate -

00:58:49.770 --> 00:58:51.920
the Watergate hearings
changed everything.

00:58:51.920 --> 00:58:53.490
And the reason it changed was

00:58:53.490 --> 00:58:58.370
because there are several
individuals who had the courage

00:58:58.370 --> 00:59:00.110
to make some really
tough decisions.

00:59:00.110 --> 00:59:03.650
And one of them was not to
necessarily broadcast them gavel

00:59:03.650 --> 00:59:05.450
to gavel because many

00:59:05.450 --> 00:59:08.610
of the stations would
not broadcast it live

00:59:08.610 --> 00:59:12.620
because they had educational
TV on during the day time.

00:59:12.620 --> 00:59:17.190
But somebody and I was part
of the mix of the somebody's,

00:59:17.190 --> 00:59:20.190
said "Why the hell don't
we run them at night?

00:59:20.190 --> 00:59:22.560
Repeat them at night"?

00:59:22.560 --> 00:59:24.190
And that was a big, big deal.

00:59:24.190 --> 00:59:25.700
It was a big decision.

00:59:25.700 --> 00:59:29.400
And the people who were running
PBS were nervous about it

00:59:29.400 --> 00:59:31.750
so they said, "Let's
poll the stations".

00:59:31.750 --> 00:59:34.950
So but we - we did
poll the stations

00:59:34.950 --> 00:59:37.450
but we polled the stations
in a very clever way.

00:59:37.450 --> 00:59:41.420
We polled the stations with
a question that was kind

00:59:41.420 --> 00:59:45.570
of phrased in such a way
"Do you want to be patriotic

00:59:45.570 --> 00:59:51.980
or do you want to be a jerk" And
we still barely won a majority.

00:59:51.980 --> 01:00:00.890
But as MacNeil said at the time
and I quote him almost verbatim,

01:00:00.890 --> 01:00:04.490
well the option - because it was
summertime and PBS didn't have

01:00:04.490 --> 01:00:07.810
that much to run at night anyway
- they had no original programs

01:00:07.810 --> 01:00:09.660
to run at night anyhow.

01:00:09.660 --> 01:00:12.470
So he said, "Well
all they would run

01:00:12.470 --> 01:00:17.940
if they didn't run the hearings
would be" - how did he put it,

01:00:17.940 --> 01:00:27.010
English speaking people
talking, animals mating,

01:00:27.010 --> 01:00:30.810
and occasionally English
speaking people mating

01:00:30.810 --> 01:00:32.610
and animals talking.

01:00:32.610 --> 01:00:38.040
[ Laughter ]

01:00:38.040 --> 01:00:39.960
So why not replace it with
the Watergate hearings?

01:00:39.960 --> 01:00:44.970
That's why when I said 3:00
a.m., the hearings weren't going

01:00:44.970 --> 01:00:47.950
on till 3:00 a.m., that
was the repeat every night.

01:00:47.950 --> 01:00:50.530
We would do it live
all day but we only had

01:00:50.530 --> 01:00:53.470
about maybe half the
stations were watching it,

01:00:53.470 --> 01:00:55.120
were broadcasting it.

01:00:55.120 --> 01:00:59.260
But at night the -
and it wouldn't -

01:00:59.260 --> 01:01:03.900
it was the old story you know,

01:01:03.900 --> 01:01:07.540
the big stations wouldn't
take it, but then they started

01:01:07.540 --> 01:01:08.840
because the word got out

01:01:08.840 --> 01:01:11.430
and then suddenly it
became a big deal.

01:01:11.430 --> 01:01:16.700
And the big deal was that
it proved beyond a shadow

01:01:16.700 --> 01:01:20.180
of a doubt that there was a
role for news and public affairs

01:01:20.180 --> 01:01:22.530
on public broadcasting because
of those hearing and out

01:01:22.530 --> 01:01:24.380
of that came the news
hour and everything else.

